<p class="myHeader">Facilities</p>
<p>Edgecumbe College is set in spacious grounds where students work and engage in recreational activities in a relaxed and well cared for environment. There are well equipped rooms for all subjects with computer aided learning used in an increasing number of subjects.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Computer Network</strong></span><br />
The school has two computer rooms, each equipped with 26 machines. All classrooms in the school are linked to the main computer network via fiber optic cable allowing students ready access to the Internet, word processing, and desktop publishing tools. Servers control internet filtering, printing, email, storage of student/teacher work and remote access. Remote access allows students and teachers to work on the school system from home using their own broadband connection. There are in excess of 150 computers within the school</p>
<p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Library</strong></span><br />
Students can access extensive amounts of information from books, CD-ROM, the Internet with a subscription to Te Puna and inter-loan facilities with the National Library. A fully computerised database networked to classes provides ease of access to library information throughout the college. Colour and plain copiers are available in the library for student use.</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: larger;">Horticulture Department</span></strong><br />
An extensive Horticulture Department with an adjacent specialist laboratory provides tutoring in agriculture and horticulture at all NCEA levels. The horticulture area covers more than 2 hectares</p>
<p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Music Suite</strong></span><br />
Our music suite along with a keyboard laboratory is due for refurbishment. It houses a huge classroom with 3 practice rooms for students undertaking lessons through the itinerant music program.<br /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Special Programs</strong></span><br />
Edgecumbe College special learning needs are catered for in the Te Whare Awhina special unit.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Gymnasium &amp; Swimming Pool</strong></span><br />
A well equipped gymnasium and large playing fields are complemented by a solar heated 30 meter swimming pool which is extensively used throughout summer by the community as well as the school.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>College Canteen</strong></span><br />
In Term 3, our canteen will be redesigned and upgraded to meet the needs of staff and students. It offers a wide range of foods. For the convenience of students, especially those who travel by bus the canteen is open before school as well as interval and lunch. All canteen profits are used to benefit the educational needs of the students. The service is run by a manager with two part-time helpers.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Student Services Center</strong></span><br />
A Student Services Center houses the Guidance Counselors and the Transition/Careers Adviser. The facility is a relaxed, warm environment where students can go at lunchtimes to access career information or, at prearranged times to see the Guidance Counselor. <br /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: larger;"><strong>Health Clinics</strong></span><br />
A Health Clinic is run in conjunction with Pacific Health. Students may access this on a regular basis. Appointments can be made through the main office. A doctor is also in attendance on a weekly basis.<br /></p>
